d groups; the warning remains a carry-forward scale signal, not a newly identified blocker in this slice.\n- Whole-project structure debt outside this cluster remains in broader shell/UI concentration reports, especially `bootstrap_page.cj` and `home_page.cj`. I did not sweep those unrelated clusters in this turn.\n\nNext recommended action:\n- Run the next requested whole-project repair cluster sweep, starting with `cluster-target-structure-whole-project-target-structure-broad-shell-endpoints`, and move feature evidence off `bootstrap_page.cj` where more precise domain/page endpoints already exist.\n\nNotes:\n- I did not edit `source-coverage-matrix.json` or `platform-capability-check.json` because the repaired behavior/evidence stayed within the existing status model; this was a code/evidence alignment fix rather than a row-status change.\n- The worktree is already dirty in many generated/report files outside my edits. I left those untouched.","time":{"start":1782667446571,"end":1782667453280}}}
